steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8cvrd","text":"The proteins were expressed in E. coli Rosetta pLySS cells. Grow the cells in 4 L of LB medium at 37°C until an OD600 nm of 0.4. Next, bring the temperature down to 18°C and grow further to an OD600 nm of 0.8. Induce protein expression with 100 μM IPTG and grow for further 16 h at 18°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":31,"length":7},{"style":"sub","offset":114,"length":6},{"style":"sub","offset":195,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"25ga8","text":"Pellet the cells at 4000 rpm    . Re-suspended the cell pellet in a lysis buffer containing 50 mM HEPES, pH 7.5, 300 mM NaCl, 2 mM MgCl2, 2 mM β-mercaptoethanol, cOmplete protease inhibitors (Roche), DNase and flash freeze in liquid nitrogen. Store in    until the day of purification.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":29,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":31,"length":1},{"key":2,"offset":252,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"15euh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"604B0590EBDA11EC9B1E01C6753C037E","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"4","unit":10}},"1":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":900,"guid":"6CA71590EBDA11EC9B1E01C6753C037E","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}},"2":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"C9B9D600EBDA11EC9B1E01C6753C037E","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"-80","unit":10}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"euah5","text":"Open the cells by thawing and sonicating 2 x 30 seconds. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"34fhu","text":"Clear the lysate by centrifugation (25 000 rpm for 30 min at 4°C in a Ti45 rotor, Beckman).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"kiko","text":"Incubate the cleared supernatant with 5 ml of Glutathione Sepharose 4B beads slurry (Cytiva) for 1h at 4°C rolling slowly. The beads slurry should be washed with water and then with 50 mM HEPES, pH 7.5, 300 mM NaCl, and 1 mM DTT beforehand.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6e7q5","text":"Finally, incubate  with TEV protease at 4°C. 20 ul of 10 mg/ml home-madeTEV protease.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":18,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"85trk","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":900,"guid":"9F8CA590EBDC11EC9B1E01C6753C037E","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":["overnight"],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fm0vg","text":"Concentrate the protein down to 0.5 ml using 30kDa cut-off Amicon filter and apply onto a Superose 6 increase column (10/300 Cytiva) pre-equillibrated with a buffer containing 25 mM HEPES, pH 7.5, 150 mM NaCl, and 1 mM DTT.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"959oh","text":"Pool fractions containing pure proteins (see attached pdf), concentrate, snap freeze in liquid nitrogen, and store at −80°C. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bb4bj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6a63","text":"Human NDP52 and human OPTN S177D S473D genes were cloned into bacterial expression vector. Addgene IDs: 187828 and 187827, respectively.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fti3h","text":"After 1h of incubation with the cleared lysate wash the beads four times with 40 ml low salt buffer (50 mM HEPES, pH 7.5, 300 mM NaCl, and 1 mM DTT) buffer, followed by one wash with high salt buffer (50 mM HEPES, pH 7.5, 700 mM NaCl, and 1 mM DTT) and again two washes with low salt buffer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4m7kf","text":"The next day spin down the beads (4000 rpm, 3 min, 4°C) and collect the supernatant containing cleaved protein. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4hrb0","text":"Filter the supernatant through a 0.45 μm syringe filter to remove any residual beads. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
